main event: A report details a UFO sighting on 20 October 1964 in Beavercreek, Ohio, involving one observed object for a duration of 12 minutes.
interesting points: The observation was classified as ground-visionary., The object was described as stationary during the observation., There was no physical evidence or photographs related to the sighting., The sighting occurred after the formation of Project Blue Book and involved a documented investigation., The report included correspondence from the Dearborn Observatory indicating skepticism about the sighting's significance.
witness description: Witness age 32, sex: Male; details about the witness and sightings provided in a questionnaire.
